name: micro-service-demo
description: This repository contains a demo project showcasing a microservices-based application, designed to provide a hands-on understanding of microservice architecture and implementation. The project consists of an API Gateway, Config Server, Discovey Server, and two microservices: Student and School

name: MaintenanceParts
description: This project aims to learn microservices through an example system for ordering parts required for Maintenance Operations. The application consists of several microservices that work together to process orders and check part availability in the warehouse.

name: banking-account-app
description: This repository contains a banking account application developed using Spring Boot with a microservices architecture. The application leverages Spring Cloud to implement distributed systems principles, ensuring scalability, resilience, and efficient inter-service communication.

name: Developpement-d-une-architecture-micro-service
description: This project is an e-commerce application built using a microservices architecture. It leverages Spring Boot and Spring Cloud to implement a scalable, decoupled system with dedicated services for billing, customer management, inventory, and more. The design includes centralized configuration, service discovery, and an API gateway.

name: Panic-Notification-System
description: a notification system utilizes a fast callback mechanism through a message queue in a Microservices setup, ensuring rapid and reliable delivery of alerts for real-time applications.

name: course-web-app
description: An example of a course and lesson management application, in where users can login, enroll in courses, view course materials, ask questions and get answers

name: JordiAragonZaragoza.Cinema
description: This project is a demonstration of a fictional Cinema Management Application. It is built on .NET, applying Domain-Driven Design and Clean Architecture principles. The solution leverages a Microservices Architecture and Event-Driven Architecture for its foundation.

name: three-context-framework
description: The Three-Context Architecture is designed to empower developers in creating high-quality, resilient microservices with a focus on organized code, robust error handling, and resilience. This framework provides a structured approach that can withstand the demands of modern applications.

name: DevOps-CI-CD-project
description: Welcome to the Azure DevOps project repository! This project showcases the deployment of a microservices-based application through an end-to-end CI/CD pipeline, from scratch. Whether you're new to DevOps or have some experience, this guide will help you understand how to automate your deployments with Azure DevOps.
